Lagos – The international friendly match between Poland and Nigeria will kick off at 8:45pm on Friday Nigeria time on Friday. This was revealed by the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) via its twitter handle on Tuesday. The two World Cup-bound national teams are using the friendly to kick start their preparations for the summer World Cup in Russia. Super Eagles started their preparation for the friendly with gym training on Tuesday morning in Warclaw, Poland. Fitness coach Jean Luc-Royer was seen working on Stephen Eze, while goalkeeper trainer Alloy Agu drilled Deportivo La Coruna’s Francis Uzoho at team’s Radisson Blu Hotel. Some of the videos of the morning training were via the team’s twitter handle, with messages such as, @NGSuperEagles: We hit the gym this morning as preparations begin in earnest for Friday’s pre World Cup friendly against Poland. We share some of the videos with you.#SoarSuperEagles. Another message in the eearly hours of Tuesday also reads @NGSuperEagles: Serious work begins as we build up to the 2018 FIFA World Cup, Russia.#SoarSuperEagles. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.